Member Function Documentation

override MethodInfo Vnvd.UserDefined.ErrorType.GetMethodImpl ( string  name,
BindingFlags  bindingAttr,
Binder  binder,
CallingConventions  callConvention,
Type[]  types,
ParameterModifier[]  modifiers 
) [protected]

When overridden in a derived class, searches for the specified method whose parameters match the specified argument types and modifiers, using the specified binding constraints and the specified calling convention.

Returns:
A T:System.Reflection.MethodInfo object representing the method that matches the specified requirements, if found; otherwise, null.
Parameters:
name The T:System.String containing the name of the method to get.
bindingAttr A bitmask comprised of one or more T:System.Reflection.BindingFlags that specify how the search is conducted.-or- Zero, to return null.
binder A T:System.Reflection.Binder object that defines a set of properties and enables binding, which can involve selection of an overloaded method, coercion of argument types, and invocation of a member through reflection.-or- null, to use the P:System.Type.DefaultBinder.
callConvention The T:System.Reflection.CallingConventions object that specifies the set of rules to use regarding the order and layout of arguments, how the return value is passed, what registers are used for arguments, and what process cleans up the stack.
types An array of T:System.Type objects representing the number, order, and type of the parameters for the method to get.-or- An empty array of the type T:System.Type (that is, Type[] types = new Type[0]) to get a method that takes no parameters.-or- null. If types is null, arguments are not matched.
modifiers An array of T:System.Reflection.ParameterModifier objects representing the attributes associated with the corresponding element in the types array. The default binder does not process this parameter.
Exceptions:
T:System.Reflection.AmbiguousMatchException More than one method is found with the specified name and matching the specified binding constraints.
T:System.ArgumentNullException name is null.
T:System.ArgumentException types is multidimensional.-or- modifiers is multidimensional.-or- types and modifiers do not have the same length.
